---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Day 1: Semantic HTML - 25 Days of A11y">
  <h1>Day 1: Semantic HTML</h1>
  
  <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol>
      <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
      <li>Day 1</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>
  
  <article>
    <header>
      <h2>Why Semantic HTML Matters</h2>
      <p><time datetime="2024-01-01">January 1, 2024</time></p>
    </header>
    
    <section>
      <h3>What is Semantic HTML?</h3>
      <p>
        Semantic HTML uses elements that clearly describe their meaning in a human- 
        and machine-readable way. Instead of using generic <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> 
        elements everywhere, we use specific elements like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, 
        <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h3>Benefits for Accessibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Screen readers can navigate content more effectively</li>
        <li>Users can skip to main content or navigation</li>
        <li>Content structure is clearer for all users</li>
        <li>Search engines better understand your content</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <h3>Example: Before vs After</h3>
      
      <h4>❌ Non-semantic</h4>
      <pre><code>&lt;div class="header"&gt;
  &lt;div class="nav"&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;Home&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="content"&gt;
  &lt;div class="article"&gt;
    &lt;div class="title"&gt;My Article&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
      
      <h4>✅ Semantic</h4>
      <pre><code>&lt;header&gt;
  &lt;nav&gt;
    &lt;a href="/"&gt;Home&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;main&gt;
  &lt;article&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;My Article&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
&lt;/main&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>
    
    <footer>
      <p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Review your existing HTML and identify places where you can use more semantic elements.</p>
    </footer>
  </article>
  
  <nav aria-label="Pagination">
    <a href="/" rel="prev">← Home</a>
    <a href="/day-2" rel="next">Day 2: Headings →</a>
  </nav>
</Layout>

<style>
  nav[aria-label="Breadcrumb"] ol {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Breadcrumb"] li::after {
    content: ">";
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Breadcrumb"] li:last-child::after {
    content: "";
  }
  
  article {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  article header {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #dee2e6;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  section {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  pre {
    background-color: #f8f9fa;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
  }
  
  code {
    background-color: #f8f9fa;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace;
  }
  
  pre code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Pagination"] {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Pagination"] a {
    color: #007bff;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #007bff;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    transition: all 0.15s ease-in-out;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Pagination"] a:hover {
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
  }
  
  nav[aria-label="Pagination"] a:focus {
    outline: 2px solid #007bff;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
